724634f-a.title: Manhattan: West Street - Hubert Street
724634f-a.folder: West Street & Hubert Street, Manhattan, NY

724633f-a.title: Manhattan: West Street - Hubert Street
724633f-a.text:
(1)
West Street, north from Bubert Street, showing foundation work
for the extension of the West Side Express Highway. For an account
of same, see the N.Y. Times of November 12, 1937. Buildings on the
right, line the east side of this street.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
N(eg ~2968
(2)
One block northward, from Laight Street. Piers on the left abut
on the North River. The 9-story structure appearing on the right is
No. 260-262 West Street, at the S.E. corner of Vestry Street (upon
which it also bears Nos. 67-73).
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
